              "page": 11,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "text": "A rules element with this trait is one-of-a-kind. The DC of Recall Knowledge checks related to creatures with this trait is increased by 10.",
          "type": "trait"
        },
        {
          "classes": [
            "size"
          ],
          "edition": "legacy",
          "game-id": "36e474dd2f4c19b317214eccf55c8c77",
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "name": "Medium",
          "sources": [
            {
              "errata": {
                "alt": "2.0",
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "2.0",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "link": {
                "alt": "Core Rulebook pg. 474",
                "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01y0k?Pathfinder-Core-Rulebook",
                "name": "Core Rulebook pg. 474",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "name": "Core Rulebook",
              "page": 474,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "text": "*Space:* 5 feet, *Reach (Tall):* 5 feet, *Reach (Long):* 5 feet",
          "type": "trait"
        },
        {
          "alternate_link": {
            "alternate_type": "legacy",
            "aonid": 207,
            "game-obj": "Traits",
            "type": "alternate_link"
          },
          "classes": [
            "monsters"
          ],
          "edition": "remastered",
          "game-id": "d3bfc0df6c75fa3d188816919a7c6bf5",
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "name": "Amphibious",
          "sources": [
            {
              "errata": {
                "alt": "2.0",
                "aonid": 216,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "2.0",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "link": {
                "alt": "Player Core pg. 452",
                "aonid": 216,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "Player Core pg. 452",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "name": "Player Core",
              "page": 452,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "text": "An amphibious creature can breathe in water and in air, even outside of its preferred environment, usually indefinitely but at least for hours. These creatures often have a swim Speed. Their bludgeoning and slashing unarmed Strikes don\u2019t take the usual \u20132 penalty for being underwater.",
          "type": "trait"
        },
        {
          "alternate_link": {
            "alternate_type": "legacy",
            "aonid": 69,
            "game-obj": "Traits",
            "type": "alternate_link"
          },
          "classes": [
            "creature_type"
          ],
          "edition": "remastered",
          "game-id": "68e0931a4aa46e583f2efa3182902f5b",
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "name": "Fey",
          "sources": [
            {
              "errata": {
                "alt": "2.0",
                "aonid": 216,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "2.0",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "link": {
                "alt": "Player Core pg. 456",
                "aonid": 216,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "Player Core pg. 456",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "name": "Player Core",
              "page": 456,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "text": "Creatures of the First World are called the fey",
          "type": "trait"
        },
        {
          "classes": [
            "monsters"
          ],
          "edition": "remastered",
          "game-id": "40b5d9c5e49dbe2aea5d7ecf38d950f3",
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "name": "Mythic",
          "sources": [
            {
              "link": {
                "alt": "War of Immortals pg. 69",
                "aonid": 232,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "War of Immortals pg. 69",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "name": "War of Immortals",
              "page": 69,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "text": "Options with this trait grant or utilize mythic power. Feats with the mythic trait can only be taken by mythic characters, who are typically characters with a mythic Calling.  \n  \n Monsters with the mythic trait have access to a pool of Mythic Points and are particularly strong for creatures of their level. Many mythic monsters are either resistant or entirely immune to attacks from non-mythic creatures and weapons.  \n  \n Spells with the mythic trait require the expenditure of a Mythic Point in order to be cast, and items with the mythic trait require the expenditure of a Mythic Point in order to use their activated abilities.  \n  \n Weapons with the mythic trait overcome the resistances and immunities of mythic monsters.",
          "type": "trait"
        },
        {
          "alternate_link": {
            "alternate_type": "legacy",
            "aonid": 230,
            "game-obj": "Traits",
            "type": "alternate_link"
          },
          "classes": [
            "monsters"
          ],
          "edition": "remastered",
          "game-id": "8582d2861f7683b85a20279c4f5f3fdf",
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "name": "Nymph",
          "sources": [
            {
              "errata": {
                "alt": "1.1",
                "aonid": 221,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "1.1",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "link": {
                "alt": "Monster Core pg. 363",
                "aonid": 221,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "Monster Core pg. 363",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "name": "Monster Core",
              "page": 363,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "text": "This family of beautiful fey creatures has strong ties to natural locations.",
          "type": "trait"
        },
        {
          "alternate_link": {
            "alternate_type": "legacy",
            "aonid": 165,
            "game-obj": "Traits",
            "type": "alternate_link"
          },
          "classes": [
            "monsters"
          ],
          "edition": "remastered",
          "game-id": "28b3ffaf7df1fef23da1eb1d9c63267d",
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "links": [
            {
              "alt": "aquatic combat",
              "aonid": 2438,
              "game-obj": "Rules",
              "name": "aquatic combat",
              "type": "link"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Water",
          "sources": [
            {
              "errata": {
                "alt": "2.0",
                "aonid": 216,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "2.0",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "link": {
                "alt": "Player Core pg. 463",
                "aonid": 216,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "Player Core pg. 463",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "name": "Player Core",
              "page": 463,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "text": "Effects with the water trait either manipulate or conjure water. Those that manipulate water have no effect in an area without water. Creatures with this trait consist primarily of water or have a connection to magical water.  \n  \nPlanes with this trait are mostly liquid. Visitors who can\u2019t breathe water or reach an air pocket likely drown. The rules for aquatic combat aquatic combat usually apply, including the inability to cast fire spells or use actions with the fire trait. Creatures with a weakness to water take damage equal to double their weakness at the end of each round.",
          "type": "trait"
        }
      ],
      "type": "stat_block_section"
    },
    "defense": {
      "ac": {
        "subtype": "armor_class",
        "type": "stat_block_section",
        "value": 30
      },
      "automatic_abilities": [
        {
          "ability_type": "automatic",
          "links": [
            {
              "alt": "weak",
              "aonid": 23,
              "game-obj": "MonsterTemplates",
              "name": "weak",
              "type": "link"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Water Dependent",
          "subtype": "ability",
          "text": "Pendidia is bonded to a spring, pond, or similar-sized water feature. If she is more than 300 feet away from it for 24 hours or more, she gains the weak adjustments until she returns. She can perform a 24-hour ritual to bond herself to a new body of water.",
          "type": "stat_block_section"
        },
        {
          "ability_type": "automatic",
          "name": "Watery Healing",
          "subtype": "ability",
          "text": "For every 10 minutes Pendidia spends soaking in her bonded body of water, she regains 45 Hit Points.",
          "traits": [
            {
              "alternate_link": {
                "alternate_type": "legacy",
                "aonid": 89,
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "type": "alternate_link"
              },
              "edition": "remastered",
              "game-id": "46d51374c2ada72347818dbac1edd7a3",
              "game-obj": "Traits",
              "name": "Healing",
              "sources": [
                {
                  "errata": {
                    "alt": "2.0",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "2.0",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "link": {
                    "alt": "Player Core pg. 457",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "Player Core pg. 457",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "name": "Player Core",
                  "page": 457,
                  "type": "source"
                }
              ],
              "text": "A healing effect restores a creature\u2019s body, typically by restoring Hit Points, but sometimes by removing diseases or other debilitating effects.",
              "type": "trait"
            },
            {
              "alternate_link": {
                "alternate_type": "legacy",
                "aonid": 134,
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "type": "alternate_link"
              },
              "edition": "remastered",
              "game-id": "60a4f011afd1e0fac8211bd01108d104",
              "game-obj": "Traits",
              "name": "Primal",
              "sources": [
                {
                  "errata": {
                    "alt": "2.0",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "2.0",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "link": {
                    "alt": "Player Core pg. 460",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "Player Core pg. 460",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "name": "Player Core",
                  "page": 460,
                  "type": "source"
                }
              ],
              "text": "This magic comes from the primal tradition, connecting to the natural world and instinct. Anything with this trait is magical.  \n  \nA creature with this trait is primarily constituted of or has a strong connection to primal magic.",
              "type": "trait"
            },
            {
              "alternate_link": {
                "alternate_type": "legacy",
                "aonid": 128,
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "type": "alternate_link"
              },
              "edition": "remastered",
              "game-id": "6571a8a0a7aae945b34252db53de1861",
              "game-obj": "Traits",
              "links": [
                {
                  "alt": "undead",
                  "aonid": 160,
                  "game-obj": "Traits",
                  "name": "undead",
                  "type": "link"
                }
              ],
              "name": "Vitality",
              "sources": [
                {
                  "errata": {
                    "alt": "2.0",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "2.0",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "link": {
                    "alt": "Player Core pg. 463",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "Player Core pg. 463",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "name": "Player Core",
                  "page": 463,
                  "type": "source"
                }
              ],
              "text": "Effects with this trait heal living creatures with energy from the Forge of Creation, deal vitality energy damage to undead, or manipulate vitality energy.  \n  \nThese planes are awash with life energy. Colors are brighter, fires are hotter, noises are louder, and sensations are more intense. At the end of each round, an undead creature takes at least minor vitality environmental damage. In the strongest areas of a vitality plane, they could take moderate or even major vitality damage instead. While this might seem safe for living creatures, vitality planes present a different danger. Living creatures regain an amount of HP each round equal to the environmental damage undead take in the same area. If this would bring the living creature above their maximum HP, any excess becomes temporary HP. Unlike normal, these temporary HP combine with each other, and they last until the creature leaves the plane. If a creature\u2019s temporary HP from a vitality plane ever exceeds its maximum HP, it explodes in a burst of overloaded vitality energy, spreading across the area to birth new souls.",
              "type": "trait"
            }
          ],
          "type": "stat_block_section"
        }
      ],
